/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/13155903/Forbidden-GX-Druid-Ziggy-Edition-specs-120x79.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/13155903/Forbidden-GX-Druid-Ziggy-Edition-specs-768x507.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/13155903/Forbidden-GX-Druid-Ziggy-Edition-specs-1536x1014.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/13155903/Forbidden-GX-Druid-Ziggy-Edition-specs-696x459.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/13155903/Forbidden-GX-Druid-Ziggy-Edition-specs-1068x705.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/13155903/Forbidden-GX-Druid-Ziggy-Edition-specs-1920x1267.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/13155903/Forbidden-GX-Druid-Ziggy-Edition-specs-636x420.jpg 636w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-261780\">*Click to see larger image. Images and video c. Forbidden Bike Co.</figcaption></figure><p>Suspension is supplied by Fox, with a Performance Elite 36 GRIP 2 150mm fork and a Performance Elite DPX2 rear shock. Dropper post lengths are 125mm for small frames, 150mm on mediums and 170mm for L/XL’s.</p><p><span><iframe width=\"696\" height=\"392\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/MaqIWzWYOvw?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;start=4&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></p><p>Enjoy this video of Dillon Butcher tossing the Ziggy Edition around some tight corners, and just in case you’re getting funny ideas about building a 27.5” Druid, 27.5” front wheels are not recommended for this frame and will void your warranty!</p><p>The GX Druid Ziggy Edition sells for $6599, and will be available as of June in North America and August in Europe.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.forbiddenbike.com/\"><em>forbiddenbike.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Steve Fisher","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"d3407137729ecb0c88fbd02592bd86936031c43327378945e72f31372661b2ab","category":"Cycling"}